div.h1: Resource Proxy and Live Resource Access
div.p: How control plane accesses workload cluster resources via agent tunnel

GET: Retrieve individual resources LIST: List resources by type/namespace WATCH: Stream resource changes (WebSocket) PATCH: Update resources (limited operations) DELETE: Delete resources (with permissions) EXEC: Execute commands in pods LOGS: Stream container logs

ul.li: Live Resource Viewing: View actual state of resources
Pod Logs: Stream logs from workload cluster
Debugging: Exec into pods for troubleshooting
All requests go through mTLS tunnel
Agent RBAC controls access on workload cluster
Audit logging of all proxy requests

pre.code: Request ID: UUID Timeout: 30s default Status: Pending Processing Complete Channel: Response channel per request

ul.li: Routes all requests to resource proxy
Additional latency vs direct cluster access
Stream must be active for proxy to work
No need to expose Kubernetes API
No VPN or network routing required
Same mTLS tunnel as config sync
